%h4 Headings

%p All headings include a <code>margin-bottom</code> and the appropriate <code>line-height</code>.

%h1
  Heading One &ndash; Book 36px
%h2
  Heading Two &ndash; Book 24px
%h3
  Heading Three &ndash; Book 21px
%h4
  Heading Four &ndash; Normal 18px
%h5
  Heading Five &ndash; Semibold 16px
%h6
  Heading Six &ndash; Semibold 14px

-# ========================================
-# Font families

%h4 Font Families

%p There are two font families available, each of which include an extendable silent class <code>[%]</code>.

%ul.sg-value-list
  %li.sg-type-families-sans-serif
    Sans-serif &ndash; Open Sans, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif
    %code.sg-value-offset %font-family-sans-serif
  %li.sg-type-families-monospace
    Monospace &ndash; Source Code Pro, Inconsolata, Lucida Console, Terminal, Courier New, Courier
    %code.sg-value-offset %font-family-monospace

-# ========================================
-# Font weights

%h4 Font Weights

%p There are three font weights available, each of which include an extendable silent class <code>[%]</code>. There are however a few rules as to how these font weights may be paired with other styles. Open Sans may only appear as italic in a normal or bold weight. Source Code Pro should never appear in a book weight or as italic.

%ul.sg-value-list
  %li.sg-type-weight-bold
    Bold &ndash; 600
    %code.sg-value-offset %font-weight-bold
  %li.sg-type-weight-normal
    Normal &ndash; 400
    %code.sg-value-offset %font-weight-normal
  %li.sg-type-weight-book
    Book &ndash; 300
    %code.sg-value-offset %font-weight-book

-# ========================================
-# Line heights

%h4 Miscellaneous Type Styles

%p Miscellaneous typography styles, all of which include an extendable silent class <code>[%]</code>.

%ul.sg-value-list
  %li
    Center Text
    %code.sg-value-offset %text-center
  %li
    Remove Text Decorations
    %code.sg-value-offset %text-decoration-none

-# ========================================
-# Line heights

%h4 Line Heights

%p There are three line heights available, each of which included a variable <code>[$]</code> and an extendable silent class <code>[%]</code>. When using a line height outright please use the <code>@extend</code> rule, however should computation be needed feel free to use one of the variables.

%ul.sg-value-list
  %li.sg-type-height-base
    Base &ndash; 22px
    %code.sg-value-offset [$, %]line-height-base
  %li.sg-type-height-double
    Double &ndash; 44px
    %code.sg-value-offset [$, %]line-height-double
  %li.sg-type-height-triple
    Triple &ndash; 66px
    %code.sg-value-offset [$, %]line-height-triple